
[1]bodkin

   BOD'KIN, n. [Gr.a thorn.]

   1. An instrument of steel; bone, ivory or the like, with a small blade,
   and a sharp point, for making holes by piercing. A like instrument with
   an eye, for drawing thread, tape, or ribin through a loop, &c. An
   instrument to dress the hair.

   2. A dagger. [Not in use.]
